      header#compileStructure.sectionHeader
        h2 Compile Structure

      p Unlike many CSS frameworks, Start is designed to work with theme files. As such, it uses its own theme file out-of-the-box. 

      h3 File structure in a nutshell

      pre theme/
        |   default.sass
        |   dark.sass
        |   light.sass
        | style.sass

      p Here's the gist:
      ol
        li Everything in 
          strong lib
          |  shouldn't be edited.
        li
          strong theme/[chosen theme].sass 
          |  defines your overall look and feel. Colors, typography, etc, but does not assign styles to the DOM.
        li
          strong style.sass
          |  will assign styles to dom elements.

