      h3 Wrappers and Frames
      p There are two important high-level containers to consider, wrappers and frames.
      p 
        strong Wrappers
        |  simply set a max width for your content, centering it if the screen exceeds that width. If you want a background color on your content, apply this to your wrapper, not the frame. The frame can be reused to apply identical margins to nested elements and shouldn't have much styling involved.
      p
        strong Frames
        |  are optional and create padding on the left and right of the content. Remember sections defined in columns will automatically have left and right padding. If you need to align elements elsewhere with that padding, simply put them in a column that is 12 wide.

