      header#fixed-pane.sectionHeader
        h2 Fixed Pane
      p The fixed pane is a full window wrapper to affix elements to the screen while still obeying the grid.
      p Effectively, this creates a full fixed pane over the entire screen in which elements can be arranged as they are anywhere else on your page.
      p
        strong For example,
        |  see the sidebar on this page.

      p Say you had this layout, where a sidebar appears on 1/3 of the screen:

      pre &lt;body&gt;
        |   &lt;main&gt;
        |     &lt;aside&gt;Sidebar&lt;/aside&gt;
        |     &lt;/section&gt;Main&lt;/section&gt;
        |   &lt;/main&gt;
        | &lt;/body&gt;
        | 
        | body { @include wrapper(); }
        | main { @include row(); }
        | aside {
        |   @include col();
        |   @include cols(4);
        | }
        | section {
        |   @include col();
        |   @include cols(8);
        | }

      p When you scroll down on the page, the sidebar will scroll with it. Here's how we can pop it out:

      pre &lt;body&gt;
        |   &lt;div class=&quot;fixed&quot;&gt;
        |     &lt;div class=&quot;body&quot;&gt;
        |       &lt;main&gt;
        |         &lt;aside&gt;Sidebar&lt;/aside&gt;
        |       &lt;/main&gt;
        |     &lt;/div&gt;
        |   &lt;/div&gt;
        |   &lt;main&gt;
        |     &lt;/section&gt;Main&lt;/section&gt;
        |   &lt;/main&gt;
        | &lt;/body&gt;
        | 
        | body, .body { @include wrapper(); }
        | main        { @include row(); }
        | aside {
        |   @include col();
        |   @include cols(4);
        | }
        | section {
        |   @include col();
        |   @include cols(8);
        |   @include bump(4);
        | }
        | .fixed { @include fixed-pane(); }

      h3 Playing nicely with mouse events
